haas center for public service stanford college prep student affairs haas center for public service students faculty alumni community about stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit stanford college prep stanford college prep background and purpose student involvement application upward bounce teach with stanford college prep stanford college prep haas center for public service program students stanford college prep scp is a direct service tutoring program offered by the haas center for public service the haas center's mission is to inspire stanford university to realize a just and sustainable world through service scholarship and community partnerships scp partners with the charter east palo alto academy high school epaahs to provide 60 first generation low income minority students with the resources and support to succeed academically in high school and go on to college stanford student mentors tutors work directly with high school students in neighboring east palo alto where about 70 of youth do not graduate stanford college prep aims to close the achievement gap by promoting and modeling academic success self development and access to resources through stanford student mentors tutors after school curriculum saturday workshops college tours summer programs and parent education workshops through scp stanford students grow into agents of positive social change for more information please contact edgar chavez in the news check out the stanford news service article on stanford college prep summer academy 2011 here background and purpose student involvement application upward bounce teach with stanford college prep background and purpose groups haas center for public service printer friendly version education & youth programs at haas east palo alto stanford acadamy jumpstart stanford college prep science in service ravenswood reads connect with us facebook facebook twitter twitter video icon video stanford seal newsletter giving to haas action log